      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "It's hard to knock the form of BLACKTHORN (1) who has put back-to-back wins together to start the career and is racing high on confidence. Has plenty of upside and only needs some luck navigating from the sticky draw to be playing a major role in the finish again. TALONS (3) put it all together over this course and distance last time out and winning rider Fry stays on top. Must be included in calculations. LOOK AT ROSA (10) is a two-time winner here who is better than the last couple of efforts suggest. Gets in well at the weights with the claim and looks a strong top-three candidate on best figures. BLUEBIRD BAY (4) wasn't too far off them when having the first run for the new stable and will strip fitter second-up from the break. In the mix. The well-related SILVER CITY (5) (half to Listed winner Tribal Wisdom) best of the rest.",
